# kubectl top

> top objects of Kubernetes objects and resources.
> More information: <https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/generated/kubectl/kubectl-commands#top>.

## Show metrics for a given pod and its containers

kubectl top pod {{pod-name}} --containers

## Show metrics for a given pod and sort it by 'cpu' or 'memory'

kubectl top pod {{pod-name}} --sort-by={{cpu|memory}}
